            . I am servant to Thomas Jackson, who is a <rs id="t18180401-50-viclabel290" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180401-50-victim386 t18180401-50-viclabel290"></join>, and lives at <placeName id="t18180401-50-crimeloc291">Knightsbridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180401-50-crimeloc291" type="placeName" value="Knightsbridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180401-50-crimeloc291" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180401-50-off288 t18180401-50-crimeloc291"></join>. On the 3d of March, I hung my basket on the railing while I went down the area-when I returned I missed the butter and cloths.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180401-50-person388">
                  GEORGE 
                  GREATOREX
               <interp inst="t18180401-50-person388" type="surname" value="GREATOREX"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-50-person388" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-50-person388" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoners opposite my shop, going across the field. Suspecting them I called to them, they ran away - I pursued them across the field into a garden. They got over several garden walls; Day had the bundle, which he threw into a ditch - I took it out-it was butter. I secured them, and am sure they are the men.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
